article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 53, Stony Brook 52
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Ed Tyson scored a game-high 20 points and Marc Davis contributed nine points, and Maryland-Eastern Shore defeated Stony Brook 53-52 Thursday. Denzel Jackson landed a free throw with six seconds remaining to hand the victory to UMES (1-1). Jackson had a game-high 10 rebounds. Stony Brook (0-3) took a lead into half time, 24-21. Michael Tyree scored a team-high 13 points for Stony Brook.
